#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code duplicate letters hata kar lexicographically smallest string banata hai using stack.

1. Pehle har character ka last occurrence index store karte hain.
   Isse pata chalta hai ki koi character future me dobara aayega ya nahi.
2. String ko left se right traverse karte hain.
3. Agar current character already result me aa chuka hai (seen = true),
   to usse skip kar dete hain.
4. Warna stack se tab tak pop karte hain jab tak:
   - stack top current character se bada ho, aur
   - stack top future me dobara aane wala ho
   Isse result lexicographically chhota banta hai.
5. Fir current character ko stack me push karke seen mark kar dete hain.
6. End me stack se string bana kar reverse kar dete hain.

Main idea:
Har character sirf ek baar rakhna hai, aur answer dictionary order me sabse chhota chahiye.
Isliye bigger characters ko hata dete hain agar wo baad me fir mil sakte hain.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

import java.util.*;

public class Solution {
    public String removeDuplicateLetters(String s) {
      //You can code here

      int n = s.length();
      //prepare a hash array and mark lastIndex of character
      int[] lastIndex = new int[26];
      for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
        lastIndex[s.charAt(i) - 'a'] = i;
      }

      Deque<Character> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();
      boolean[] seen = new boolean[26];

      for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
        char ch = s.charAt(i);
        //if already exist in stack then skip iteration
        if(seen[ch - 'a']) continue;

        //pop until stack is empty && current character is smaller than stack.top and also stack.top element
        // must be available in the string in future
        while(!stack.isEmpty() && stack.peek() > ch && lastIndex[stack.peek() - 'a'] > i){
          seen[stack.pop() - 'a'] = false;
        }

        //otherwise just normally add the character and mark it as seen for to eliminate duplicacy
        stack.push(ch);
        seen[ch - 'a'] = true;
      }

      //Now make a stringBuilder and do the operations 
      StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
      while(!stack.isEmpty()){
        sb.append(stack.pop());
      }

      sb.reverse();
      return sb.toString();

  }
}
